                        <interp inst="t18351123-name-876" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD CHISWELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Mr. George Evans; he lives in Tottenham-court-road, and is a linen draper. The prisone was in his employ—on the 21st of November, about half-past one o'clock, I saw him take two pieces of silk serge from off the counter, and put them into his hat, which was on the floor—he then put his hat on his head, and walked out with it—this is one pieces of the silk.</p>
